data.title: Trieste First Issues
data.text:
Trieste, Zones A and B

1st October 1947 and 1948

↓

Description Scott# SG# Mi# Y&T# Zone A, overprints of Italian stamps 25 centesimi greenish blue 1 1 other values 50c to 100 lire 2-14 2-17 † Zone B, perf 10½x11, no wm, lithographed 1 lira carmine-red and stone 1 B2 Italian ‡ 2 B3 Croatian 3 B1 Slovene

† Gibbons' initial listing block includes three overprints issued in 1948, Sc15-17.

‡ The inscriptions can be seen on the block shown above: Italian MAGGIO; Croation SVIBANJ; Slovene MAJ.

Scott lists Zone A under Italian Offices and Zone B under Yugoslavia. Gibbons lists both Zones under Trieste in Part 3, Balkans.
